	* C/ HOW TO RUN

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A/ REQUIREMENTS

Zelda should function on any standard 64bit Linux environment with
gcc and clang. A good amount of physical memory (16GB to start with, more is no luxury)
is recommended. 

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
B/ COMPILING INSTRUCTIONS

Normally, with a GNU environment, just type:

> make

Zelda biniary can be found in the ./bin directory

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
C/ HOW TO RUN

Type

> ./bin/Zelda -h 

to get a help, how to use Zelda

Example:

> cd example
> bash example.sh

Runs a test assembly on the basis of a given Illumina HiSeq2500 dataset of the Enterobacteria phage lambda.
Creates example/Lambda folder with DB and Assembly sub-folder.

DB  	     Contains the input reads in a compressed database representation
Assembly     All intermediate assembly files and the finished assembly in contigs.fasta/scaffolds.fasta

